<<
/Type /StructElem
/S /H3
/P 48 0 R
/T (Highway toll collection is an essential process for maintaining road infrastructure and managing transportation revenue. Traditionally, toll collection has been performed manually where vehicles stop at toll booths and make payments to operators. This manual process often results in traffic congestion, delays, and difficulties in maintaining accurate transaction records. To improve efficiency, toll management systems can be automated using software that handles vehicle identification, toll calculation, and transaction recording. Automation reduces manual work, speeds up toll processing, and ensures better data management. This project presents the design and implementation of a Smart Toll Collection System using C++. The system simulates the operations of a toll plaza by allowing vehicles to be registered, processing toll payments, and storing transaction records. The application uses object-oriented programming principles and file handling techniques to organise data and manage toll transactions efficiently.)
/E (Highway toll collection is an essential process for maintaining road infrastructure and managing transportation revenue. Traditionally, toll collection has been performed manually where vehicles stop at toll booths and make payments to operators. This manual process often results in traffic congestion, delays, and difficulties in maintaining accurate transaction records. To improve efficiency, toll management systems can be automated using software that handles vehicle identification, toll calculation, and transaction recording. Automation reduces manual work, speeds up toll processing, and ensures better data management. This project presents the design and implementation of a Smart Toll Collection System using C++. The system simulates the operations of a toll plaza by allowing vehicles to be registered, processing toll payments, and storing transaction records. The application uses object-oriented programming principles and file handling techniques to organise data and manage toll transactions efficiently.)
/Pg 10 0 R
/K [9 10]
>>
endobj
