/Type /StructElem
/S /H3
/P 49 0 R
/T (system allows users to register vehicles, process toll payments, and maintain transaction records through a menu-driven interface. The application uses object-oriented programming concepts to represent vehicles, toll booths, and system operations. Toll charges are calculated automatically based on the type of vehicle. All toll transactions are recorded in a text file, allowing the system to maintain a history of payments. The system also generates receipts for each toll transaction and tracks revenue statistics for each toll booth. This project demonstrates how programming techniques such as classes, arrays, functions, and file handling can be applied to simulate a real-world toll management system.)
/E (system allows users to register vehicles, process toll payments, and maintain transaction records through a menu-driven interface. The application uses object-oriented programming concepts to represent vehicles, toll booths, and system operations. Toll charges are calculated automatically based on the type of vehicle. All toll transactions are recorded in a text file, allowing the system to maintain a history of payments. The system also generates receipts for each toll transaction and tracks revenue statistics for each toll booth. This project demonstrates how programming techniques such as classes, arrays, functions, and file handling can be applied to simulate a real-world toll management system.)
/Pg 11 0 R
/K [13 14]
