/T (1. The user launches the program and views the main menu. 2. A vehicle can be registered by entering its details. 3. When a vehicle arrives at a toll booth, the user selects a booth and enters the vehicle plate number. 4. The system calculates the toll based on the vehicle type. 5. The toll payment is processed and recorded in a transaction log. 6. A receipt is generated for the payment. 7. The system updates booth statistics including total revenue and vehicle count.)
/E (1. The user launches the program and views the main menu. 2. A vehicle can be registered by entering its details. 3. When a vehicle arrives at a toll booth, the user selects a booth and enters the vehicle plate number. 4. The system calculates the toll based on the vehicle type. 5. The toll payment is processed and recorded in a transaction log. 6. A receipt is generated for the payment. 7. The system updates booth statistics including total revenue and vehicle count.)
