/T (Vehicle Class The Vehicle class stores information related to vehicles including plate number, owner name, and vehicle type. This class is responsible for storing and displaying vehicle information. TollBooth Class The TollBooth class represents individual toll booths and stores details such as booth ID, booth location, total revenue collected, and number of vehicles processed. Each booth keeps track of its operational statistics. TollSystem Class The TollSystem class controls the overall functionality of the program. Its responsibilities include registering vehicles, processing toll payments, calculating toll charges, logging transaction records, generating receipts, and displaying booth statistics.)
/E (Vehicle Class The Vehicle class stores information related to vehicles including plate number, owner name, and vehicle type. This class is responsible for storing and displaying vehicle information. TollBooth Class The TollBooth class represents individual toll booths and stores details such as booth ID, booth location, total revenue collected, and number of vehicles processed. Each booth keeps track of its operational statistics. TollSystem Class The TollSystem class controls the overall functionality of the program. Its responsibilities include registering vehicles, processing toll payments, calculating toll charges, logging transaction records, generating receipts, and displaying booth statistics.)
/Pg 12 0 R
/K [14 15]
