204 0 obj
<<
/Type /StructElem
/S /H3
/P 52 0 R
/T (application and perform different operations such as registering vehicles, processing tolls, and viewing booth statistics. Static Array for Vehicle Storage: Vehicle records are stored in a fixed-size array within the system. This approach simplifies data management in a console-based application and avoids the overhead of dynamic memory allocation for a simulation context. Transaction Logging: Every toll payment is recorded in transactions.txt with the date, vehicle details, booth ID, and toll amount. This provides administrators with a complete and persistent history of all transactions. Receipt Generation: After processing a toll payment, the system generates a dedicated receipt file named using the vehicle's plate number. This makes it easy to retrieve individual transaction records.)
/E (application and perform different operations such as registering vehicles, processing tolls, and viewing booth statistics. Static Array for Vehicle Storage: Vehicle records are stored in a fixed-size array within the system. This approach simplifies data management in a console-based application and avoids the overhead of dynamic memory allocation for a simulation context. Transaction Logging: Every toll payment is recorded in transactions.txt with the date, vehicle details, booth ID, and toll amount. This provides administrators with a complete and persistent history of all transactions. Receipt Generation: After processing a toll payment, the system generates a dedicated receipt file named using the vehicle's plate number. This makes it easy to retrieve individual transaction records.)
/Pg 14 0 R
/K [19 20]
