217 0 obj
<<
/Type /StructElem
/S /H3
/P 53 0 R
/T (Conclusion The Smart Toll Collection System demonstrates how software can improve the efficiency of toll management operations. By automating vehicle identification, toll calculation, and transaction recording, the system reduces manual work and improves operational accuracy. The project highlights the practical application of object-oriented programming and file handling in C++ to develop a structured toll management simulation. The modular class-based design ensures the codebase is maintainable and extensible. With further development, the system could be expanded to include database integration for persistent vehicle storage, a graphical user interface, digital payment support, and integration with real-time traffic monitoring hardware.)
/E (Conclusion The Smart Toll Collection System demonstrates how software can improve the efficiency of toll management operations. By automating vehicle identification, toll calculation, and transaction recording, the system reduces manual work and improves operational accuracy. The project highlights the practical application of object-oriented programming and file handling in C++ to develop a structured toll management simulation. The modular class-based design ensures the codebase is maintainable and extensible. With further development, the system could be expanded to include database integration for persistent vehicle storage, a graphical user interface, digital payment support, and integration with real-time traffic monitoring hardware.)
/Pg 15 0 R
/K [12 13]
>>
